    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Printed cards made on the occasion of a person's death, usually distributed at funeral ceremonies. Often the name and life dates of the deceased are printed along with a religious text and image.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000022451/Bodleian Library, John Johnson Collection (1971)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>因人們去世而印製的卡片，通常於喪禮上發送；卡片上除了往生者的名字與生卒年份之外，一般還印有宗教性的文章及圖像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
